8
00:00:52,553 --> 00:00:54,653
 narrator: the metal bistro set 

9
00:00:54,655 --> 00:00:57,189
         is a fixture in        
      european-style cafés      

10
00:00:57,191 --> 00:00:59,157
     and small restaurants.     

11
00:00:59,159 --> 00:01:02,962
   the set consists of a small  
  dining table and two chairs.  

12
00:01:02,964 --> 00:01:07,399
 a bistro set is also popular in
homes with limited outdoor space

13
00:01:07,401 --> 00:01:09,301
       as there's usually       
       enough room for one      

14
00:01:09,303 --> 00:01:13,205
  on a balcony or small patio.  

15
00:01:13,207 --> 00:01:16,074
    the small restaurant bar    
       known as the bistro      

16
00:01:16,076 --> 00:01:19,144
           originated           
     in 19th century france.    

17
00:01:19,146 --> 00:01:22,615
     its iconic dining sets     
 are still being produced today 

18
00:01:22,617 --> 00:01:27,118
       in both traditional      
       and modern styles.       

19
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:30,188
 this french factory makes them 
   out of strips of flat steel  

20
00:01:30,190 --> 00:01:32,591
       with rounded edges.      

21
00:01:32,593 --> 00:01:34,727
        the first step is       
      to flatten the strip      

22
00:01:34,729 --> 00:01:37,530
 with pressure-applying rollers.

23
00:01:39,533 --> 00:01:41,600
  the steel then enters a press 

24
00:01:41,602 --> 00:01:44,803
   which does three operations  
         simultaneously.        

25
00:01:44,805 --> 00:01:47,306
        it cuts pieces to       
      the required length,      

26
00:01:47,308 --> 00:01:51,644
 rounds their ends, and punches 
    out holes where required.   

27
00:01:51,646 --> 00:01:55,981
         these are parts        
       for the table legs.      

28
00:01:55,983 --> 00:01:58,617
           meanwhile,           
  this computer-guided machine  

29
00:01:58,619 --> 00:02:02,588
   bends a 1/2-inch steel rod   
  into a circle to form a ring  

30
00:02:02,590 --> 00:02:04,556
 that will support the tabletop.

31
00:02:04,558 --> 00:02:10,396
                     ♪♪         

32
00:02:10,398 --> 00:02:12,330
   this table is collapsible,   

33
00:02:12,332 --> 00:02:15,367
    allowing it to fold flat    
          for storage.          

34
00:02:15,369 --> 00:02:18,003
   therefore, two of the legs   
           are hinged.          

35
00:02:18,005 --> 00:02:21,206
    a pin and notch lock them   
      in the open position.     

36
00:02:23,410 --> 00:02:26,077
     after putting together     
        the folding legs,       

37
00:02:26,079 --> 00:02:28,681
     a worker positions all     
     the parts for the base     

38
00:02:28,683 --> 00:02:30,849
     on an assembly fixture.    

39
00:02:30,851 --> 00:02:33,652
        then he operates        
        a welding robot,        

40
00:02:33,654 --> 00:02:35,821
 which welds all the crossbars, 

41
00:02:35,823 --> 00:02:41,393
      reinforcing the legs      
    and the legs to the ring.   

42
00:02:41,395 --> 00:02:44,396
  it only takes about 2 minutes 
     to weld all these parts    

43
00:02:44,398 --> 00:02:46,599
   into a folding table base.   

44
00:02:50,371 --> 00:02:52,538
        the manufacturers       
        make the tabletop       

45
00:02:52,540 --> 00:02:55,207
       from a square piece      
         of sheet steel.        

46
00:02:55,209 --> 00:02:57,643
    this machine first sheers   
        off the corners,        

47
00:02:57,645 --> 00:21:17,308
     transforming the square    
         into a circle.         

